  "description": "Backport of the Armor Trims from 1.20",
  "body": "<div align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Hipposgrumm/armor-trims/master/images/banner.png\" alt=\"Armor Trims Backport\" title=\"Do you like my white and gold armor trim?\"></div><br>\nArmor Trims Backport allows you to decorate your armor with various materials.<br>\n<br>\nWhen interacting with a smithing table, this is what you'll see instead of the normal GUI:<br>\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Hipposgrumm/armor-trims/master/images/guiShow.png\" alt=\"A modified smithing table GUI featuring a smithing template slot and an armor stand.\"><br>\nRegular smithing recipes can still be laid out as normal, ignoring the smithing template slot.<br>\nThis excludes netherite upgrading—which has been disabled in favor of the Netherite Upgrade Smithing Template, but can be reenabled if you so desire.<br>\n<br>\nTrims are visible on the player (obviously) and are also displayed on the item.<!-- Off the record, this wasn't easy to simply plop in. -->\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Hipposgrumm/armor-trims/master/images/armorShow.png\" alt=\"Hipposgrumm (aka the mod developer) wearing iron armor trimmed with emerald in the pattern Flow.\"><br>\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Hipposgrumm/armor-trims/master/images/itemShow.png\" alt=\"A display of trimmed armors in item frames: Turtle Helmet with Redstone, Netherite Chestplate with Diamond, Gold Leggings with Lapis, and Leather Boots with Quartz.\">",
